<doc id="558089" wikidata="Q1935644" url="?curid=558089" title="Primal Scream (Primal Scream album)">
<text>Primal Scream is the second studio album by Scottish rock band Primal Scream. It was released on 4 September 1989 in the United Kingdom by Creation Records and in the United States by Mercenary Records. Musically, it took a harder rock approach than their 1987 debut &quot;Sonic Flower Groove&quot; and did not achieve great success. However, the song &quot;I&#x27;m Losing More Than I&#x27;ll Ever Have&quot; was later remixed to provide the breakthrough single &quot;Loaded&quot;, which appeared on their much celebrated third album &quot;Screamadelica&quot;.

==Critical reception==

The album received mixed-to-positive reviews from music critics. Tim Sendra of AllMusic wrote: &quot;While the group was capable of whipping up a credible approximation of thuggish hard rock, Bobby Gillespie&#x27;s fragile wisp of a voice is rather ill-suited to kicking out the jams.&quot;

==Track listing==
==Personnel==
Credits adapted from liner notes.
;Primal Scream
* Robert &quot;Throb&quot; Young – guitar
* Bobby Gillespie – vocals
* Andrew Innes – guitar
* Philip Tomanov – drums
;Additional musicians
* Henry Olsen – bass, orchestration
* Martin Duffy – piano
;Technical
*Alan McGee – management
*Jayne Houghton – cover photography

